gurmukhi: ਮਿਲੀ ਰਾਜ ਦਾਜੰ ਸੁ ਦਾਸੀ ਅਨੂਪੰ ॥
translation: The King janmeja received a unique maid-servant in his dowry,
Who was very learned and supremely beautiful.

gurmukhi: ਮਿਲੇ ਹੀਰ ਚੀਰੰ ਕਿਤੇ ਸੁਅਾੳੁ ਕਰਨੰ ॥
transliteration: Mile Heer Chderan Kite Suaau Karnaan||
translation: He also received diamonds, garments and horses of black ears;

gurmukhi: ਮਿਲੇ ਮੱਤ ਦੰਤੀ ਕਿਤੇ ਸੇਤ ਬਰਨੰ ॥੧੮॥੧੮੬॥
translation: He also got many wanton white-coloured elephants with tusks.18.186.
On his marriage, the king became very happy.

gurmukhi: ਭਲੀ ਭਾਂਤ ਪੋਖੇ ਦਿਜੰ ਸਰਬ ਅੰਨੰ ॥
translation: All the Brahmin were satisfied with the grant of all types of corn.

gurmukhi: ਕਰੇ ਭਾਂਤ ਭਾਂਤੰ ਮਹਾ ਗਜ ਦਾਨੰ ॥
transliteration: Dare Bhaant Bhaantan Mahaa Gad Daanaaan||
translation: The king gave in charity various of elephants.

gurmukhi: ਭੲੇ ਦੋੲਿ ਪੁਤ੍ਰੰ ਮਹਾਂ ਰੂਪ ਮਾਨੰ ॥੧੯॥੧੮੭॥
transliteration: Bhae Doe Poutran Mahaan Roop Maanan||19||187||
translation: From both his wives, two very beautiful sons were born.19.187.
(One day) the king saw the winsome maid-servant.

gurmukhi: ਮਨੋ ਚੀਰ ਕੈ ਚਾਰ ਚੰਦ੍ਰਾ ਨਿਕਾਸੀ ॥
transliteration: Mano Cheer Kai Chaar Channdraa Nikaasee||
translation: He felt as if the moonlight hath penetrated out of the moon.

gurmukhi: ਲਹੈਂ ਚੰਚਲਾ ਚਾਰ ਬਿਦਿਅਾ ਲਤਾ ਸੀ ॥
transliteration: Lahain Channdhalaa Chaar Bidiaa Lataa See||
translation: He considered her as beautiful lightning and as creeper of learning;

gurmukhi: ਕਿਧੌ ਕੰਜ ਕੀ ਮਾਂਝ ਸੋਭਾ ਪ੍ਰਕਾਸੀ ॥੨੦॥੧੮੮॥
translation: Or the inner glory of the lotus hath manifested itself.20.188.

gurmukhi: ਕਿਧੌ ਫੂਲ ਮਾਲਾ ਲਖੇ ਚੰਦ੍ਰਮਾ ਸੀ ॥
transliteration: Kidhau Phool Maalaa Lakhe Channdramaa See||
translation: It seemd as if she was a garland of flowers or the moon itself;

gurmukhi: ਕਿਧੌ ਪਦਮਨੀ ਮੈ ਬਨੀ ਮਾਲਤੀ ਸੀ ॥
translation: It may be the flower of Malti or it may be Padmini,
